{\H1.2x;\C3;1.00   \LGENERAL\l\C4;\P}1.01  ALL DIMENSIONS ARE IN SI UNITS. \P1.02  WORK TO FIGURED DIMENSIONS AND DO NOT SCALE THE DRAWING. \P1.03  ALL STRUCTURAL DRAWINGS SHALL BE READ IN CONJUNCTION WITH\P        RELEVANT ARCHITECTURAL AND SERVICE 
  3
DRAWINGS. \P1.04 DIMENSIONS AND CONDITIONS MUST BE VERIFIED IN THE SITE. AND ANY  \P        DISCREPANCIES SHALL BE BROUGHT TO THE NOTICE OF THE STRUCTURAL \P        DESIGN TEAM BEFORE PROCEEDING WITH THE AFFECTED PART OF THE  WORK.\P1.05  ALL LEVELS 
  3
OF THE PROJECT REFERS TO ARCHITECTURAL DRAWING. \P1.06  THE STRUCTURE IS DESIGNED FOR : \P         BASEMENT+G+1+TERRACE+HEAD ROOM & OHT FLOORS ONLY.  \P1.07 THE STRUCTURE IS DESIGNED TO BE SELF SUPPORTING AND STABLE AFTER THE  \P        BUILDING IS C
  3
OMPLETE. IT IS \P        THE CONTRACTORS RESPONSIBILITY TO DETERMINE ERECTION PROCEDURES\P        AND SEQUENCE TO INSURE SAFETY OF THE BUILDING AND ITS COMPONENTS  \P        DURING ERECTION. THIS INCLUDES THE ADDITION OF NECESSARY SHORING, \P        
  3
SHEETING, TEMPORARY BRACING, GUYS, OR TIE DOWNS.\P1.08 PROPOSED CHANGES OR SUBSTITUTIONS TO STRUCTURAL DETAILS OR PLANS \P        SHALL BE SUBMITTED TO THE  DESIGN ENGINEER FOR REVIEW AND APPROVAL.\P1.09 STRUCTURE IS CONVENTIONAL SYSTEM FROM FOUNDATI
  1
ON TO SUPER STRUCTURE. 
  7
