{\H1.2x;\C3;5.00   \LBASEMENT CONSTRUCTION AND DEWATERING}\P\P\pxi-3,l3,qd;5.01  IN ORDER TO AVOID FLOATATION, DEWATERING SHALL BE REDUCED ONLY AS THE SUPERSTRUCTURE WEIGHT INCREASES. UNLESS IT CAN BE SHOWN OTHERWISE BY THE CONTRACTOR, THE GROUNDWATE
  3
R LEVELS SHALL BE MAINTAINED DURING THE CONSTRUCTION AT BELOW THE SOFFIT OF THE FOUNDATION. THE DEWATERING SYSTEM MAY BE REMOVED ONCE THE CONSTRUCTION OF THE STRUCTURE  IS COMPLETED.\P\pqj;5.02  BACKFILLING WITH SELECTED EARTH BEHIND RETAINING WALLS 
  3
SHALL BEGIN ONLY AFTER THE CONSTRUCTION OF GROUND FLOOR SLAB AND AS APPROVED BY THE ENGINEER.                                                                       \P5.03  ANY MAJOR ISSUES RELATED TO DEWATERING SHALL BE BROUGHT TO THE NOTICE OF THE S
  1
OIL / SHORING CONSULTANTS AND ALL OTHER PROJECT STAKE HOLDERS BEFORE EXECUTION. 
