  3
P^Ia. SLABS UPTO 4.5M 7 DAYS OVER 4.5M 14 DAYS \P^Ib. BEAMS UPTO 6.0M 14 DAYS OVER  6.0M 21 DAYS\P^Ic. WALL/BEAM/COLUMN VERTICAL FACES  24 HOURS\P\PSHUTTERING CAN BE RELEASED EARLIER THAN SPECIFIED ABOVE PROVIDED THE PROPS ARE \PRETAINED AT REASONABLE S
  3
PACINGS AND CONCRETE ATTAINS THE FULL STRENGTH AT THE TIME OF \PDESHUTTERING AS PER IS 456 - 2000. DESHUTTERING SHALL BE DONE BY PROVIDING DAMPENING \PMATERIAL BELOW IN ORDER TO REDUCE THE IMPACT AT THE LOWER LEVEL.\PSIMPLY SUPPORTED AND CONTINUOUS S
  3
PANS SHALL BE DESHUTTERED FROM MID SPAN \PTOWARDS SUPPORTS. CANTILEVERS SHALL BE DESHUTTERED FROM FREE END TOWARDS SUPPORTS. \PSLAB/BEAMS SHALL BE REPROPPED  UNTIL THE NEXT LEVEL SLAB IS CAST AND DESHUTTERED. \P\H1.2x;\L\C3;CONSTRUCTION JOINTS\Froman
  3
c|c0;\H1.3333x;\l }\P{\fSwis721 LtCn BT|b0|i0|c0|p34;\H0.625x;\C6;SLABS    : AT ONE THIRD OF THE SPAN FROM SUPPORT.\PBEAMS   : AT ONE THIRD OF THE SPAN FROM SUPPORT.\P IF ANY CROSS BEAMS ARE LOCATED IN THIS REGION THE JOINT SHALL  BE LOCATED TWO TIME
  3
S THE \P WIDTH OF THE BEAM AWAY FROM THE BEAM. \PRETAINING WALL :  AT THE JUNCTION OF THE WALL AND FOOTING WITH A WALL KEY JOINT AND AT \P                             MIDDLE OF VERTICAL SPAN, JOINTS TO BE AVOIDED. \PRAFT SLAB :  AT ONE THIRD OF THE S
  3
PAN FROM SUPPORT. \P                     CONSTRUCTION JOINTS SHALL BE STRAIGHT. \PCANTILEVERS : CONSTRUCTION JOINT SHALL NOT BE PROVIDED IN CANTILEVERS.\PWATER STOPPER & NECESSARY MEASURES SHALL BE TAKEN CARE ALL CONSTRUCTION JOINTS \PAS PER RELEVANT
  3
 IS CODES.\P\H1.2x;\L\C3;\P\P^J\P\P\P\P\PADMIXTURE\P\pa0.66667,sm1.07917;\H0.83333x;\l\C6;CONCRETE ADMIXTURE SHALL BE USED TO IMPROVE WORKABILITY OR STRENGTH AS \PMANUFACTURER SPECIFICATION.\PWATERPROOFING ADMIXTURE SHALL BE USED FOR WATER RETAINING S
  3
TRUCTURES, PODIUM, TERRACES, AND LIQUID STORAGE STRUCTURES.\P\pa0.25,s*;\H1.2x;\L\C3;GROUT\H0.83333x;\l\C6;\P\pa0.66667,sm1.07917;CEMENT BASED NON-SHRINK GROUT WITH A MINIMUM 7 - DAY CUBE STRENGTH OF 35 N/MM\A1;\H1.25x;\S2^ ;\S ^ ;\H0.8x;SHALL BE USED.
